description: Keep every PAW program compiled by this project public
alwaysApply: true
---

# Public PAW Programs

- Every PAW compile request in this repository must set `public: true`
  explicitly.
- This applies to built-in, evaluation, and user-prepared topic programs,
  including both Standard and Finetuned compilers.
- Never change a PAW program to private, unlisted, hidden, or ephemeral unless
  the user explicitly requests that exact policy change.
- Tests covering compilation must assert `public is True`.
- Treat public visibility as a deliberate product requirement, not a privacy
  default that the agent may reinterpret.
- Prepare prompts are sent to the public PAW compiler, so user-facing
  documentation must warn users not to include sensitive information.
